gameRecap.title: Game Recap: 76ers 124, Magic 109
gameRecap.excerpt: The Sixers win their fourth straight game and improve to 27-13 on the year as they defeat the Magic, 124-109. Joel Embiid totaled 36 points and seven rebounds as Tyrese Maxey added 32 points and five assists, this is the ninth time this season the duo has gone for 30 or more each. Wendell Carter Jr. went for a season-high 25 points and 11 rebounds as Paolo Banchero added 14 points, eight rebounds, and six assists. The Magic moved to 22-20 on the year as theyve lost four of their last six games.
